
Project : gcp-kubectl-expressjs-sample

GCP Project build and submit into Google Repository - 

Step -1 :
 
 Create a cluster with name "demo-cluster-app" with min node 3. ( It will take fews mins to create a cluster )
 
 1.) gcloud container clusters create demo-cluster-app --num-nodes=3
 
Step-2 :

 Build and submit Docker images into Google Registry. 

  1.) gcloud contain builds submit --tag gcr.io/$PROJECT_ID/kub_node1.0 .

Step 3)

Once Cluster i.e demo-cluster-app is created then execute below deployment and service yaml file as given below.

1.) kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
2.) kubectl get deployment // Check the deployment is applied correctly.
3.) kubectl apply -f service.yaml
4.) kubectl get svc // Check the service is applied correctly.

